  "prompt": "What is origin of \"Nehru\" surname?",
  "response": "The surname \"Nehru\" has its origins in India and is most commonly associated with the Nehru family, particularly Jawaharlal Nehru, who was the first Prime Minister of India after independence. The name \"Nehru\" is believed to be derived from the Hindi word \"nehru,\" which means \"river bank\" or \"river.\" It is thought that the name originally referred to a location or a family that lived by a river.\n\nThe Nehru family has its roots in the Kashmir Valley, and they were known to be a prominent family in the region. The family's ancestral home was in the town of Anantnag in Kashmir. Over time, members of the Nehru family moved to Delhi, where they became actively involved in politics and public service.\n\nIn summary, the surname \"Nehru\" reflects geographical and cultural aspects of Indian history and is most notably associated with Jawaharlal Nehru and his descendants.",
